<item>
            <title>[PAY-3609] 3.1 ACH Per-Transaction Limit Alert &amp; Test Coverage</title>
                <link>https://wellfit.atlassian.net/browse/PAY-3609</link>
                <project id="10016" key="PAY">Payments</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As a compliance officer,&lt;br/&gt;
I want confirmation that ACH per-transaction limit breach alerts work identically to CP/CNP alerts,&lt;br/&gt;
So that the Compliance team has complete visibility across all payment rails without any coverage gaps.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This story verifies that the PerTransactionLimitExceededProcessor (implemented in Epic 1, Stories 1.1/1.2) correctly processes ACH-rail Payment.Debit.Submitted events published by the already-shipped ACH Transaction Limits feature (
    &lt;span class=&quot;jira-issue-macro resolved&quot; data-jira-key=&quot;PAY-3213&quot; &gt;
                &lt;a href=&quot;https://wellfit.atlassian.net/browse/PAY-3213&quot; class=&quot;jira-issue-macro-key issue-link&quot;  title=&quot;ACH Transaction Limits&quot; &gt;
            &lt;img class=&quot;icon&quot; src=&quot;https://wellfit.atlassian.net/images/icons/issuetypes/epic.svg&quot; /&gt;
            PAY-3213
        &lt;/a&gt;
                                                    &lt;span class=&quot;aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-subtle aui-lozenge-success jira-macro-single-issue-export-pdf&quot;&gt;Closed&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;/span&gt;
). No processor code changes are expected &#8212; the processor is rail-agnostic by design (ADR-006). The work is test coverage, fixture creation, and dev-environment smoke testing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;AcceptanceCriteria&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Acceptance Criteria&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;BusinessCriteria%28NonTechnical%29&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Business Criteria (Non-Technical)&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;*Given an ACH transaction that exceeds the merchant&apos;s configured per-transaction limit is declined&lt;br/&gt;
When the Compliance Monitor processes the resulting event&lt;br/&gt;
Then an email alert is sent to the Compliance inbox with the same content as CP/CNP alerts (merchant name, merchant ID, configured limit, attempted amount, timestamp, percentage above limit, and rail: &quot;ACH&quot;)*&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;*Given an ACH daily-limit breach event arrives at the per-transaction processor&lt;br/&gt;
When the processor evaluates the event&lt;br/&gt;
Then no email is sent (the sibling AchDailyLimitExceededProcessor handles daily-limit events)*&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;AC1%3AACHPerTransactionEvent%E2%80%94AlertSent&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;AC-1: ACH Per-Transaction Event &#8212; Alert Sent&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Given a Payment.Debit.Submitted event with status: &quot;Declined&quot;, declineReason: &quot;PerTransactionLimitExceeded&quot;, rail: &quot;ACH&quot;, and configuredTransactionLimit present&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When processed by PerTransactionLimitExceededProcessor&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Then email is generated via IEmailContentService.GeneratePerTransactionLimitExceededContent() with rail: &quot;ACH&quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;And email is sent to ComplianceSettings.TransactionLimitAlertRecipient&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;And AlertSent is logged at Information level with subMerchantId, rail: &quot;ACH&quot;, declineReason, attemptedAmount, configuredLimit&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;And EventGridResult.Acknowledge is returned&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;AC2%3AACHDailyLimitEvent%E2%80%94CorrectlySkipped&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;AC-2: ACH Daily-Limit Event &#8212; Correctly Skipped&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Given a Payment.Debit.Submitted event with status: &quot;Declined&quot;, declineReason: &quot;DailyLimitExceeded&quot;, rail: &quot;ACH&quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When the per-transaction processor evaluates the event&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Then AlertSkipped is logged at Information level with skipReason: &quot;NonMatchingDeclineReason&quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;And no email is sent, EventGridResult.Acknowledge is returned&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;AC3%3ARoutingDispatchVerification&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;AC-3: Routing Dispatch Verification&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Given a Payment.Debit.Submitted event with declineReason: &quot;PerTransactionLimitExceeded&quot; and rail: &quot;ACH&quot; &#8212; When IPaymentEventProcessingService routes the event &#8212; Then dispatched to IPerTransactionLimitExceededProcessor (not IAchDailyLimitExceededProcessor)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Given a Payment.Debit.Submitted event with declineReason: &quot;DailyLimitExceeded&quot; and rail: &quot;ACH&quot; &#8212; When IPaymentEventProcessingService routes the event &#8212; Then dispatched to IAchDailyLimitExceededProcessor (not IPerTransactionLimitExceededProcessor)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;AC4%3AACHContractTestFixture&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;AC-4: ACH Contract Test Fixture&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Given a contract test fixture payment-debit-submitted-declined-ach-pertx-event.json&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When deserialized into PaymentDebitSubmittedEvent&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Then all fields populate correctly including rail: &quot;ACH&quot;, status: &quot;Declined&quot;, declineReason: &quot;PerTransactionLimitExceeded&quot;, configuredTransactionLimit&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;And the fixture mirrors the real payload shape produced by the shipped ACH Transaction Limits publisher&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;AC5%3AEmailContentRailDisambiguation&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;AC-5: Email Content Rail Disambiguation&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Given an ACH per-transaction limit breach is processed&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When GeneratePerTransactionLimitExceededContent() generates the email&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Then the email body includes rail: &quot;ACH&quot; so Compliance can distinguish ACH alerts from CP/CNP alerts&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;And all other email fields (merchant name, merchant ID, limit, amount, timestamp, percentage) are identical in format to CP/CNP&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;AC6%3ADevEnvironmentSmokeTest&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;AC-6: Dev Environment Smoke Test&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Given the PerTransactionLimitExceededProcessor is deployed to the dev environment&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When an ACH per-transaction limit breach is triggered (via existing ACH Transaction Limits enforcement in Payments V2)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Then the event flows through EG Domain -&amp;gt; SB topic payments -&amp;gt; SB subscription compliance-monitor-api -&amp;gt; processor -&amp;gt; email sent&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;And the email arrives at the configured Compliance inbox&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;TechnicalRequirements&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Technical Requirements&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Create payment-debit-submitted-declined-ach-pertx-event.json fixture in Tests/Application/ApplicationTests/Fixtures/ &#8212; based on the real payload shape from the ACH Transaction Limits publisher (validate against PaymentHandlerAchLimitTests in Payments V2)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Add ACH-rail test cases to PerTransactionLimitExceededProcessorTests.cs: ACH + PerTransactionLimitExceeded -&amp;gt; email sent, AlertSent logged with rail: &quot;ACH&quot;; ACH + DailyLimitExceeded -&amp;gt; no email, AlertSkipped; ACH + PerTransactionLimitExceeded + null configuredTransactionLimit -&amp;gt; no email, AlertSkipped&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Add routing dispatch test in PaymentEventProcessingServiceTests.cs: ACH per-tx event -&amp;gt; dispatched to IPerTransactionLimitExceededProcessor; ACH daily-limit event -&amp;gt; dispatched to IAchDailyLimitExceededProcessor&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Execute dev-environment smoke test: trigger ACH per-tx breach via Payments V2, verify full pipeline. Document smoke test results in story completion notes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;RequirementsFulfilled&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Requirements Fulfilled&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;FR11: ACH per-transaction limit breach detection and compliance email alert&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;NFR1: Zero latency on transaction response (inherited &#8212; event-driven architecture)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;NFR2: Async processing via Event Grid -&amp;gt; Service Bus (inherited)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;NFR3: No code on transaction path (inherited &#8212; publisher already shipped)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;Relations&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Relations&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Blocked by: Story 1.1 (processor implementation, event routing with declineReason dispatch, framework EGD flip)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Blocked by: Story 1.2 (rule evaluation, email generation with rail parameter, observability)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Related to: Stories 2.1, 2.2 (CP/CNP publishers &#8212; validates the single-processor-all-rails design)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Related to: ACH Transaction Limits feature (
    &lt;span class=&quot;jira-issue-macro resolved&quot; data-jira-key=&quot;PAY-3213&quot; &gt;
                &lt;a href=&quot;https://wellfit.atlassian.net/browse/PAY-3213&quot; class=&quot;jira-issue-macro-key issue-link&quot;  title=&quot;ACH Transaction Limits&quot; &gt;
            &lt;img class=&quot;icon&quot; src=&quot;https://wellfit.atlassian.net/images/icons/issuetypes/epic.svg&quot; /&gt;
            PAY-3213
        &lt;/a&gt;
                                                    &lt;span class=&quot;aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-subtle aui-lozenge-success jira-macro-single-issue-export-pdf&quot;&gt;Closed&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;/span&gt;
) &#8212; the publisher is already in production&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;VibeCode&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Vibe Code&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Existing test pattern to mirror:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Tests/Application/ApplicationTests/Services/EventProcessors/Payments/AchDailyLimitExceededProcessorTests.cs &#8212; reference for ACH-specific processor test structure&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;PaymentHandlerAchLimitTests.cs in Payments V2 &#8212; reference for real ACH decline event shape (282 passing tests, validates the canonical schema in production)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;NotesforAIAgent&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Notes for AI Agent&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;FIRST TASK (validation &#8212; 5 min): Read PaymentHandlerAchLimitTests.cs in the Payments V2 test project. Find the test that validates the Payment.Debit.Submitted event payload on ACH per-transaction limit breach. Extract the exact field names and values &#8212; use those to build the ACH fixture. Do NOT assume the fixture shape from the architecture doc alone.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;No processor code changes expected. The PerTransactionLimitExceededProcessor is rail-agnostic &#8212; it filters on declineReason, not rail. If ACH events fail to process correctly, the root cause is likely a schema mismatch between the ACH publisher and the processor event model. Debug the schema, not the processor logic.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Routing test is critical. The declineReason-based dispatch in IPaymentEventProcessingService is the boundary that determines whether an ACH event goes to the per-tx processor or the daily-limit processor. Test both paths explicitly.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Smoke test protocol: Use the dev environment existing ACH transaction flow. Create a test merchant with a per-transaction limit below the test amount. Submit an ACH debit exceeding the limit. Verify: (a) Payments V2 returns a decline, (b) Payment.Debit.Submitted event published to EG Domain, (c) event delivered to SB, (d) PerTransactionLimitExceededProcessor processes the event, (e) email arrives. Document each step outcome.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Do NOT modify the existing AchDailyLimitExceededProcessor. It remains a separate processor (ADR-006 deferred consolidation). Only verify that declineReason-based routing prevents cross-dispatch.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
</description>
